                broken door seal, a malfunctioning defrost timer, or blocked air
                vents. While some homeowners might attempt a DIY freezer repair
                by manually defrosting the appliance, it's usually better to
                schedule a service appointment with a professional. Our
                factory-trained technicians at Same Day Appliance Repair can
                diagnose the underlying cause of the frost buildup and perform
                the necessary repairs or replacements. Regular freezer
                maintenance can help prevent frost buildup, ensuring your
                appliance operates efficiently and extends its lifespan.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="content__page-desc">
              <h3>Electrical Issues</h3>
